              Hosting Plan FAQ

              What is the difference between Hostinger Cloud and Agency plans?

              Resources & capacity: Agency plans offer more resources, allowing you to host more websites or handle higher-traffic sites. Website isolation & security: Each website on an Agency plan is isolated. This means that if one site gets infected with malware, your other sites remain unaffected. Access per site: While Cloud plans allow sharing access to the entire account, Agency plans let you give clients access to specific websites only. Advanced functionality: Agency plans include enhanced features, such as a staging environment with selective deployment. Unlike Cloud plans, you can choose exactly what to push to production (files and or databases).

              I already have a website at Hostinger. Can I move it to an Agency plan?

              While there's no automated upgrade from other Hostinger plans to an Agency plan yet, you can easily move your site using the Clone Website feature. Once cloned, connecting your domains takes just a few clicks. If you don't have time to do it yourself, our priority technical support team can handle the migration for you.

              I already have a website. Can I migrate it to Hostinger?

              Yes - website migration is free. If you have a website built with an open-source CMS (such as WordPress) and wish to migrate your website to Hostinger, our migration team would happily do this for you. Learn more about website migration.

              Can I upgrade my plan later?

              Upgrading your Cloud hosting service is easy, automatic, and quick. We pride ourselves on having no downtime during the upgrade, so your website will be up and running the whole time. You won't have to worry about a bad browsing experience or losing revenue.
